{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"This is a representation of your brain,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and your brain can be broken into two parts."},{"time":6000,"text":"There's the left half, which is the logical side,"},{"time":8000,"text":"and then the right half,"},{"time":10000,"text":"which is the intuitive."},{"time":12000,"text":"And so if we had a scale to measure the aptitude of each hemisphere,"},{"time":15000,"text":"then we can plot our brain."},{"time":17000,"text":"And for example, this would be somebody who's completely logical."},{"time":20000,"text":"This would be someone who's entirely intuitive."},{"time":24000,"text":"So where would you put your brain on this scale?"},{"time":27000,"text":"Some of us may have opted for one of these extremes,"},{"time":30000,"text":"but I think for most people in the audience,"},{"time":32000,"text":"your brain is something like this --"},{"time":34000,"text":"with a high aptitude in both hemispheres at the same time."},{"time":37000,"text":"It's not like they're mutually exclusive or anything."},{"time":39000,"text":"You can be logical and intuitive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41000,"text":"And so I consider myself one of these people,"},{"time":44000,"text":"along with most of the other experimental quantum physicists,"},{"time":47000,"text":"who need a good deal of logic"},{"time":49000,"text":"to string together these complex ideas."},{"time":51000,"text":"But at the same time, we need a good deal of intuition"},{"time":54000,"text":"to actually make the experiments work."},{"time":56000,"text":"How do we develop this intuition? Well we like to play with stuff."},{"time":59000,"text":"So we go out and play with it, and then we see how it acts,"},{"time":62000,"text":"and then we develop our intuition from there."},{"time":65000,"text":"And really you do the same thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"So some intuition"},{"time":69000,"text":"that you may have developed over the years"},{"time":71000,"text":"is that one thing is only in one place at a time."},{"time":75000,"text":"I mean, it can sound weird to think about"},{"time":78000,"text":"one thing being in two different places at the same time,"},{"time":82000,"text":"but you weren't born with this notion, you developed it."},{"time":85000,"text":"And I remember watching a kid playing on a car stop."},{"time":88000,"text":"He was just a toddler and he wasn't very good at it, and he kept falling over."},{"time":91000,"text":"But I bet playing with this car stop taught him a really valuable lesson,"},{"time":94000,"text":"and that's that large things don't let you get right past them,"},{"time":98000,"text":"and that they stay in one place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"And so this is a great conceptual model to have of the world,"},{"time":104000,"text":"unless you're a particle physicist."},{"time":106000,"text":"It'd be a terrible model for a particle physicist,"},{"time":108000,"text":"because they don't play with car stops,"},{"time":110000,"text":"they play with these little weird particles."},{"time":113000,"text":"And when they play with their particles,"},{"time":115000,"text":"they find they do all sorts of really weird things --"},{"time":117000,"text":"like they can fly right through walls,"},{"time":120000,"text":"or they can be in two different places at the same time."},{"time":124000,"text":"And so they wrote down all these observations,"},{"time":127000,"text":"and they called it the theory of quantum mechanics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"And so that's where physics was at a few years ago;"},{"time":134000,"text":"you needed quantum mechanics"},{"time":136000,"text":"to describe little, tiny particles."},{"time":138000,"text":"But you didn't need it"},{"time":140000,"text":"to describe the large, everyday objects around us."},{"time":144000,"text":"This didn't really sit well with my intuition,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and maybe it's just because I don't play with particles very often."},{"time":150000,"text":"Well, I play with them sometimes,"},{"time":152000,"text":"but not very often."},{"time":154000,"text":"And I've never seen them."},{"time":156000,"text":"I mean, nobody's ever seen a particle."},{"time":159000,"text":"But it didn't sit well with my logical side either."},{"time":162000,"text":"Because if everything is made up of little particles"},{"time":165000,"text":"and all the little particles"},{"time":167000,"text":"follow quantum mechanics,"},{"time":169000,"text":"then shouldn't everything just follow quantum mechanics?"},{"time":174000,"text":"I don't see any reason why it shouldn't."},{"time":177000,"text":"And so I'd feel a lot better about the whole thing"},{"time":179000,"text":"if we could somehow show"},{"time":181000,"text":"that an everyday object"},{"time":183000,"text":"also follows quantum mechanics."},{"time":185000,"text":"So a few years ago, I set off to do just that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188000,"text":"So I made one."},{"time":191000,"text":"This is the first object"},{"time":193000,"text":"that you can see"},{"time":195000,"text":"that has been in a mechanical quantum superposition."},{"time":198000,"text":"So what we're looking at here"},{"time":200000,"text":"is a tiny computer chip."},{"time":202000,"text":"And you can sort of see this green dot right in the middle."},{"time":205000,"text":"And that's this piece of metal I'm going to be talking about in a minute."},{"time":208000,"text":"This is a photograph of the object."},{"time":210000,"text":"And here I'll zoom in a little bit. We're looking right there in the center."},{"time":213000,"text":"And then here's a really, really big close-up of the little piece of metal."},{"time":216000,"text":"So what we're looking at is a little chunk of metal,"},{"time":218000,"text":"and it's shaped like a diving board, and it's sticking out over a ledge."},{"time":221000,"text":"And so I made this thing"},{"time":223000,"text":"in nearly the same way as you make a computer chip."},{"time":225000,"text":"I went into a clean room with a fresh silicon wafer,"},{"time":228000,"text":"and then I just cranked away at all the big machines for about 100 hours."},{"time":231000,"text":"For the last stuff, I had to build my own machine --"},{"time":233000,"text":"to make this swimming pool-shaped hole"},{"time":236000,"text":"underneath the device."},{"time":238000,"text":"This device has the ability"},{"time":240000,"text":"to be in a quantum superposition,"},{"time":242000,"text":"but it needs a little help to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"Here, let me give you an analogy."},{"time":246000,"text":"You know how uncomfortable it is to be in a crowded elevator?"},{"time":249000,"text":"I mean, when I'm in an elevator all alone, I do all sorts of weird things,"},{"time":252000,"text":"but then other people get on board"},{"time":254000,"text":"and I stop doing those things"},{"time":256000,"text":"because I don't want to bother them,"},{"time":258000,"text":"or, frankly, scare them."},{"time":261000,"text":"So quantum mechanics says"},{"time":263000,"text":"that inanimate objects feel the same way."},{"time":266000,"text":"The fellow passengers for inanimate objects"},{"time":268000,"text":"are not just people,"},{"time":270000,"text":"but it's also the light shining on it"},{"time":272000,"text":"and the wind blowing past it and the heat of the room."},{"time":275000,"text":"And so we knew, if we wanted to see"},{"time":277000,"text":"this piece of metal behave quantum mechanically,"},{"time":280000,"text":"we're going to have to kick out all the other passengers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282000,"text":"And so that's what we did."},{"time":284000,"text":"We turned off the lights,"},{"time":286000,"text":"and then we put it in a vacuum and sucked out all the air,"},{"time":288000,"text":"and then we cooled it down"},{"time":290000,"text":"to just a fraction of a degree above absolute zero."},{"time":292000,"text":"Now, all alone in the elevator,"},{"time":294000,"text":"the little chunk of metal is free to act however it wanted."},{"time":296000,"text":"And so we measured its motion."},{"time":298000,"text":"We found it was moving in really weird ways."},{"time":300000,"text":"Instead of just sitting perfectly still, it was vibrating,"},{"time":303000,"text":"and the way it was vibrating was breathing something like this --"},{"time":306000,"text":"like expanding and contracting bellows."},{"time":308000,"text":"And by giving it a gentle nudge,"},{"time":310000,"text":"we were able to make it both vibrate"},{"time":312000,"text":"and not vibrate"},{"time":314000,"text":"at the same time --"},{"time":316000,"text":"something that's only allowed with quantum mechanics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319000,"text":"So what I'm telling you here is something truly fantastic."},{"time":322000,"text":"What does it mean for one thing"},{"time":324000,"text":"to be both vibrating and not vibrating"},{"time":326000,"text":"at the same time?"},{"time":328000,"text":"So let's think about the atoms."},{"time":330000,"text":"So in one case:"},{"time":332000,"text":"all the trillions of atoms that make up that chunk of metal"},{"time":335000,"text":"are sitting still"},{"time":337000,"text":"and at the same time those same atoms"},{"time":339000,"text":"are moving up and down."},{"time":341000,"text":"Now it's only at precise times when they align."},{"time":344000,"text":"The rest of the time they're delocalized."},{"time":346000,"text":"That means that every atom"},{"time":348000,"text":"is in two different places at the same time,"},{"time":350000,"text":"which in turn means the entire chunk of metal"},{"time":353000,"text":"is in two different places."},{"time":355000,"text":"I think this is really cool."},{"time":357000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":359000,"text":"Really."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":364000,"text":"It was worth locking myself in a clean room to do this for all those years"},{"time":369000,"text":"because, check this out,"},{"time":371000,"text":"the difference in scale"},{"time":373000,"text":"between a single atom and that chunk of metal"},{"time":375000,"text":"is about the same as the difference"},{"time":377000,"text":"between that chunk of metal and you."},{"time":379000,"text":"So if a single atom can be in two different places at the same time,"},{"time":382000,"text":"that chunk of metal can be in two different places,"},{"time":385000,"text":"then why not you?"},{"time":387000,"text":"I mean, this is just my logical side talking."},{"time":391000,"text":"So imagine if you're in multiple places at the same time,"},{"time":395000,"text":"what would that be like?"},{"time":398000,"text":"How would your consciousness"},{"time":400000,"text":"handle your body being delocalized in space?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":404000,"text":"There's one more part to the story."},{"time":406000,"text":"It's when we warmed it up,"},{"time":408000,"text":"and we turned on the lights and looked inside the box,"},{"time":411000,"text":"we saw that the piece metal was still there in one piece."},{"time":415000,"text":"And so I had to develop this new intuition,"},{"time":418000,"text":"that it seems like all the objects in the elevator"},{"time":421000,"text":"are really just quantum objects"},{"time":423000,"text":"just crammed into a tiny space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425000,"text":"You hear a lot of talk"},{"time":427000,"text":"about how quantum mechanics says that everything is all interconnected."},{"time":430000,"text":"Well, that's not quite right."},{"time":432000,"text":"It's more than that; it's deeper."},{"time":435000,"text":"It's that those connections,"},{"time":437000,"text":"your connections to all the things around you,"},{"time":440000,"text":"literally define who you are,"},{"time":443000,"text":"and that's the profound weirdness of quantum mechanics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}